      <h1 class='title'>Younger Travellers</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 30 April 2003 vol 404 c18WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_18ws' title='Col. 18WS &mdash; HC Deb 30 April 2003 vol 404 c18WS' name='column_18ws' href='#column_18ws' rel='bookmark'>18WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0404P0_20030430_CWS_3'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-mike-obrien' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0404P0_20030430_CWS_3' title='Link to this speech by Mr Mike O'Brien' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-mike-obrien" title="Mr Mike O'Brien">The Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs (Mr. Mike O'Brien)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">Research shows that 16&#x2013;30 year olds are the least prepared of all British travellers. Today, therefore, the Government is launching a special campaign aimed at younger travellers. It will offer vital information to help young Britons avoid getting into difficulties overseas by making them aware of some simple precautions they can take before heading off.</p><p>The campaign will offer advice to those taking a range of trips, from weekend breaks, gap years, or summer package holidays to those going off on adventure sports trips or on honeymoon.</p><p>Overseas travel is an important opportunity for young people. But we need to ensure that the experience is not spoilt by unnecessary problems or accidents. Time spent on research and preparation in advance of a trip can save a great deal of trouble and heartache later.</p><p>Every year people have distressing experiences. Most think that it could never happen to them. Sadly, it can and it does. That's why the Government is launching this campaign.</p><p>This youth mini-campaign forms part of the FCO's ongoing Know Before You Go campaign which, working with over 160 travel industry partners, encourages travellers to be better prepared before travelling overseas. The FCO website <a class='resolved-url' href="http://www.fco.gov.uk/knowbeforeyougo/">www.fco.gov.uk/knowbeforeyougo/</a> provides tips for travel overseas including guidance on taking out travel insurance, travel advice and checklists for specific groups such as backpackers and independent travellers, gay, lesbian, bisexual and transgender travellers, women travellers and those visiting friends and relatives overseas.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
